QUESTION: Terraform script to terminate EC2 instances that are in stopped state.

ANSWER:

Terraform can query stopped instances and run AWS CLI to terminate them.

Terraform Script:

provider "aws" {
  region = "us-east-1"
}

data "aws_instances" "stopped_instances" {
  filter {
    name   = "instance-state-name"
    values = ["stopped"]
  }
}

resource "null_resource" "terminate_stopped" {

  provisioner "local-exec" {
    command = "aws ec2 terminate-instances --instance-ids ${join(" ", data.aws_instances.stopped_instances.ids)}"
  }
}

Flow:

Terraform
→ fetch stopped EC2 instances
→ collect instance IDs
→ run terminate command

